30 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
31  MODULE DEFINITION FOR MULTIPLE INCLUSION
32 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
33 #ifndef STM8AF_STM8S_H
34 #define STM8AF_STM8S_H
35 
36 /* Check the used compiler */
37 #if defined(__CSMC__)
38  #define _COSMIC_
39 #elif defined(__RCST7__)
40  #define _RAISONANCE_
41 #elif defined(__ICCSTM8__)
42  #define _IAR_
43 #elif defined(__SDCC)
44  #define _SDCC_
45  #define SDCC_VERSION (__SDCC_VERSION_MAJOR * 10000 \
46  + __SDCC_VERSION_MINOR * 100 \
47  + __SDCC_VERSION_PATCH)
48 #else
49  #error in 'STM8AF_STM8S.h': compiler not supported
50 #endif
51 
52 
53 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
54  MEMORY WIDTH
55 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
56 
57 // if memory sizes [B] are not given, assume smallest available in family
58 #if !defined(STM8_PFLASH_SIZE)
59  #warning undefined STM8_PFLASH_SIZE, assume minimum
60  #define STM8_PFLASH_SIZE 2048 ///< size of program flash [B]
61 #endif
62 #if !defined(STM8_RAM_SIZE)
63  #warning undefined STM8_RAM_SIZE, assume minimum
64  #define STM8_RAM_SIZE 1024 ///< size of RAM [B]
65 #endif
66 #if !defined(STM8_EEPROM_SIZE)
67  #warning undefined STM8_EEPROM_SIZE, assume minimum
68  #define STM8_EEPROM_SIZE 128 ///< size of data EEPROM [B]
69 #endif
70 
71 // memory start / end addresses
72 #define STM8_PFLASH_START 0x8000 ///< first address in program flash
73 #define STM8_PFLASH_END (STM8_PFLASH_START + STM8_PFLASH_SIZE - 1) ///< last address in program flash
74 #define STM8_RAM_START 0x0000 ///< first address in RAM
75 #define STM8_RAM_END (STM8_RAM_START + STM8_RAM_SIZE - 1) ///< last address in RAM
76 #define STM8_EEPROM_START 0x4000 ///< first address in EEPROM
77 #define STM8_EEPROM_END (STM8_EEPROM_START + STM8_EEPROM_SIZE - 1) ///< last address in EEPROM
78 
79 // address space width (>32kB flash exceeds 16bit, as flash starts at 0x8000)
80 #if (STM8_PFLASH_END <= 0xFFFF)
81  #define STM8_ADDR_WIDTH 16 ///< width of address space
82  #define STM8_MEM_POINTER_T uint16_t ///< address variable type
83 #else
84  #define STM8_ADDR_WIDTH 32 ///< width of address space
85  #define STM8_MEM_POINTER_T uint32_t ///< address variable type
86 #endif
87 
88 
89 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
90  COMPILER SPECIFIC SETTINGS
91 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
92 
93 // Cosmic compiler
94 #if defined(_COSMIC_)
95 
96  // macros to unify ISR declaration and implementation
97  #define ISR_HANDLER(func,irq) @far @interrupt void func(void) ///< handler for interrupt service routine
98  #define ISR_HANDLER_TRAP(func) void @far @interrupt func(void) ///< handler for trap service routine
99 
100  // common assembler instructions
101  #define NOP() _asm("nop") ///< perform a nop() operation (=minimum delay)
102  #define DISABLE_INTERRUPTS() _asm("sim") ///< disable interrupt handling
103  #define ENABLE_INTERRUPTS() _asm("rim") ///< enable interrupt handling
104  #define TRIGGER_TRAP _asm("trap") ///< trigger a trap (=soft interrupt) e.g. for EMC robustness (see AN1015)
105  #define WAIT_FOR_INTERRUPT() _asm("wfi") ///< stop code execution and wait for interrupt
106  #define ENTER_HALT() _asm("halt") ///< put controller to HALT mode
107  #define SW_RESET() (_WWDG_CR = _WWDG_CR_WDGA) ///< reset controller via WWDG module
108 
109  // data type in bit fields
110  #define _BITS unsigned int ///< data type in bit structs (follow C90 standard)
111 
112 // Raisonance Compiler
113 #elif defined(_RAISONANCE_)
114 
115  // include intrinsic functions
116  #include <intrins.h>
117 
118  // macros to unify ISR declaration and implementation
119  #define ISR_HANDLER(func,irq) void func(void) interrupt irq ///< handler for interrupt service routine
120  #define ISR_HANDLER_TRAP(func) void func(void) trap ///< handler for trap service routine
121 
122  // common assembler instructions
123  #define NOP() _nop_() ///< perform a nop() operation (=minimum delay)
124  #define DISABLE_INTERRUPTS() _sim_() ///< disable interrupt handling
125  #define ENABLE_INTERRUPTS() _rim_() ///< enable interrupt handling
126  #define TRIGGER_TRAP _trap_() ///< trigger a trap (=soft interrupt) e.g. for EMC robustness (see AN1015)
127  #define WAIT_FOR_INTERRUPT() _wfi_() ///< stop code execution and wait for interrupt
128  #define ENTER_HALT() _halt_() ///< put controller to HALT mode
129  #define SW_RESET() (_WWDG_CR = _WWDG_CR_WDGA) ///< reset controller via WWDG module
130 
131  // data type in bit fields
132  #define _BITS unsigned int ///< data type in bit structs (follow C90 standard)
133 
134 // IAR Compiler
135 #elif defined(_IAR_)
136 
137  // include intrinsic functions
138  #include <intrinsics.h>
139 
140  // macros to unify ISR declaration and implementation
141  #define ISR_HANDLER(func,irq) __interrupt void func(void) ///< handler for interrupt service routine
142  //#define ISR_HANDLER_TRAP(func) void func(void) trap ///< handler for trap service routine
143 
144  // common assembler instructions
145  #define NOP() __no_operation() ///< perform a nop() operation (=minimum delay)
146  #define DISABLE_INTERRUPTS() __disable_interrupt() ///< disable interrupt handling
147  #define ENABLE_INTERRUPTS() __enable_interrupt() ///< enable interrupt handling
148  #define TRIGGER_TRAP __trap() ///< trigger a trap (=soft interrupt) e.g. for EMC robustness (see AN1015)
149  #define WAIT_FOR_INTERRUPT() __wait_for_interrupt() ///< stop code execution and wait for interrupt
150  #define ENTER_HALT() __halt() ///< put controller to HALT mode
151  #define SW_RESET() (_WWDG_CR = _WWDG_CR_WDGA) ///< reset controller via WWDG module
152 
153  // data type in bit fields
154  #define _BITS unsigned char ///< data type in bit structs (deviating from C90 standard)
155 
156 // SDCC compiler
157 #elif defined(_SDCC_)
158 
159  // macros to unify ISR declaration and implementation
160  #define ISR_HANDLER(func,irq) void func(void) __interrupt(irq) ///< handler for interrupt service routine
161  #if SDCC_VERSION >= 30403 // traps require >=v3.4.3
162  #define ISR_HANDLER_TRAP(func) void func() __trap ///< handler for trap service routine
163  #else
164  #error traps require SDCC >=3.4.3. Please update!
165  #endif
166 
167  // common assembler instructions
168  #define NOP() __asm__("nop") ///< perform a nop() operation (=minimum delay)
169  #define DISABLE_INTERRUPTS() __asm__("sim") ///< disable interrupt handling
170  #define ENABLE_INTERRUPTS() __asm__("rim") ///< enable interrupt handling
171  #define TRIGGER_TRAP __asm__("trap") ///< trigger a trap (=soft interrupt) e.g. for EMC robustness (see AN1015)
172  #define WAIT_FOR_INTERRUPT() __asm__("wfi") ///< stop code execution and wait for interrupt
173  #define ENTER_HALT() __asm__("halt") ///< put controller to HALT mode
174  #define SW_RESET() (_WWDG_CR = _WWDG_CR_WDGA) ///< reset controller via WWDG module
175 
176  // data type in bit fields
177  #define _BITS unsigned int ///< data type in bit structs (follow C90 standard)
178 
179 #endif
180

182 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
183  DEFINITION OF GLOBAL MACROS/#DEFINES
184 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
185 
186 // general macros
187 #define _SFR(type, addr) (*((volatile type*) (addr))) ///< peripheral register
188 #if defined(_DOXYGEN) || defined(UID_AddressBase)
189  #define _UID(N) _SFR(uint8_t, UID_AddressBase+N) ///< read unique identifier byte N
190 #endif
191 #if defined(_DOXYGEN) || defined(DEVID_AddressBase)
192  #define _DEVID(N) _SFR(uint8_t, DEVID_AddressBase+N) ///< read device identifier byte N
193 #endif

196 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
197  STANDARD DATA TYPES
198 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
199 #if defined(_COSMIC_) || defined(_RAISONANCE_) || defined(_IAR_)
200 
201  // skip if already defined
202  #ifndef INT8_MAX
203 
204  // compiler specific --> If possible, use <stdint.h> from compiler
205  typedef signed long int32_t;
206  typedef signed short int16_t;
207  typedef signed char int8_t;
208 
209  typedef unsigned long uint32_t;
210  typedef unsigned short uint16_t;
211  typedef unsigned char uint8_t;
212 
213 
214  // define min/max values
215  #define INT8_MAX 0x7f
216  #define INT8_MIN (-INT8_MAX - 1)
217 
218  #define UINT8_MAX 0xFF
219  #define UINT8_MIN 0
220 
221  #define INT16_MAX 0x7fff
222  #define INT16_MIN (-INT16_MAX - 1)
223 
224  #define UINT16_MAX 0xFFFF
225  #define UINT16_MIN 0
226 
227  #define INT32_MAX 0x7fffffffL
228  #define INT32_MIN (-INT32_MAX - 1L)
229 
230  #define UINT32_MAX 0xFFFFFFFF
231  #define UINT32_MIN 0
232 
233  #endif // INT8_MAX
234 
235 #elif defined(_SDCC_)
236 
237  // use compiler header
238  #include <stdint.h>
239 
240 #endif

243 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
244  ISR Vector Table (SDCC, Raisonance, IAR)
245  Note: IAR has an IRQ offset of +2 compared to STM8 datasheet (see below)
246 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
247 
248 #define __TLI_VECTOR__ 0 ///< irq0 - External Top Level interrupt (TLI) for pin PD7
249 #define __AWU_VECTOR__ 1 ///< irq1 - Auto Wake Up from Halt interrupt (AWU)
250 #define __CLK_VECTOR__ 2 ///< irq2 - Clock Controller interrupt
251 #define __PORTA_VECTOR__ 3 ///< irq3 - External interrupt 0 (GPIOA)
252 #define __PORTB_VECTOR__ 4 ///< irq4 - External interrupt 1 (GPIOB)
253 #define __PORTC_VECTOR__ 5 ///< irq5 - External interrupt 2 (GPIOC)
254 #define __PORTD_VECTOR__ 6 ///< irq6 - External interrupt 3 (GPIOD)
255 #define __PORTE_VECTOR__ 7 ///< irq7 - External interrupt 4 (GPIOE)
256 #if defined(CAN_AddressBase)
257  #define __CAN_RX_VECTOR__ 8 ///< irq8 - CAN receive interrupt (shared with \__PORTF_VECTOR__)
258 #endif
259 #if defined(PORTF_AddressBase)
260  #define __PORTF_VECTOR__ 8 ///< irq8 - External interrupt 5 (GPIOF, shared with \__CAN_RX_VECTOR__)
261 #endif
262 #if defined(CAN_AddressBase)
263  #define __CAN_TX_VECTOR__ 9 ///< irq9 - CAN transmit interrupt
264 #endif
265 #define __SPI_VECTOR__ 10 ///< irq10 - SPI End of transfer interrupt
266 #define __TIM1_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__ 11 ///< irq11 - TIM1 Update/Overflow/Trigger/Break interrupt
267 #define __TIM1_CAPCOM_VECTOR__ 12 ///< irq12 - TIM1 Capture/Compare interrupt
268 #if defined(TIM2_AddressBase)
269  #define __TIM2_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__ 13 ///< irq13 - TIM2 Update/overflow interrupt (shared with \__TIM5_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__)
270 #endif
271 #if defined(TIM5_AddressBase)
272  #define __TIM5_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__ 13 ///< irq13 - TIM5 Update/overflow interrupt (shared with \__TIM2_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__)
273 #endif
274 #if defined(TIM2_AddressBase)
275  #define __TIM2_CAPCOM_VECTOR__ 14 ///< irq14 - TIM2 Capture/Compare interrupt (shared with \__TIM5_CAPCOM_VECTOR__)
276 #elif defined(TIM5_AddressBase)
277  #define __TIM5_CAPCOM_VECTOR__ 14 ///< irq14 - TIM5 Capture/Compare interrupt (shared with \__TIM2_CAPCOM_VECTOR__)
278 #endif
279 #if defined(TIM3_AddressBase)
280  #define __TIM3_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__ 15 ///< irq15 - TIM3 Update/overflow interrupt
281 #endif
282 #if defined(TIM3_AddressBase)
283  #define __TIM3_CAPCOM_VECTOR__ 16 ///< irq16 - TIM3 Capture/Compare interrupt
284 #endif
285 #if defined(UART1_AddressBase)
286  #define __UART1_TXE_VECTOR__ 17 ///< irq17 - USART/UART1 send (TX empty) interrupt
287 #endif
288 #if defined(UART1_AddressBase)
289  #define __UART1_RXF_VECTOR__ 18 ///< irq18 - USART/UART1 receive (RX full) interrupt
290 #endif
291 #define __I2C_VECTOR__ 19 ///< irq19 - I2C interrupt
292 #if defined(UART2_AddressBase)
293  #define __UART2_TXE_VECTOR__ 20 ///< irq20 - UART2 send (TX empty) interrupt (shared with \__UART3_TXE_VECTOR__ and \__UART4_TXE_VECTOR__)
294 #elif defined(UART3_AddressBase)
295  #define __UART3_TXE_VECTOR__ 20 ///< irq20 - UART3 send (TX empty) interrupt (shared with \__UART2_TXE_VECTOR__ and \__UART4_TXE_VECTOR__)
296 #elif defined(UART4_AddressBase)
297  #define __UART4_TXE_VECTOR__ 20 ///< irq20 - UART4 send (TX empty) interrupt (shared with \__UART2_TXE_VECTOR__ and \__UART3_TXE_VECTOR__)
298 #endif
299 #if defined(UART2_AddressBase)
300  #define __UART2_RXF_VECTOR__ 21 ///< irq21 - UART2 receive (RX full) interrupt (shared with \__UART3_RXF_VECTOR__ and \__UART4_RXF_VECTOR__)
301 #elif defined(UART3_AddressBase)
302  #define __UART3_RXF_VECTOR__ 21 ///< irq21 - UART3 receive (RX full) interrupt (shared with \__UART2_RXF_VECTOR__ and \__UART4_RXF_VECTOR__)
303 #elif defined(UART4_AddressBase)
304  #define __UART4_RXF_VECTOR__ 21 ///< irq21 - UART4 receive (RX full) interrupt (shared with \__UART2_RXF_VECTOR__ and \__UART3_RXF_VECTOR__)
305 #endif
306 #if defined(ADC1_AddressBase)
307  #define __ADC1_VECTOR__ 22 ///< irq22 - ADC1 end of conversion (shared with \__ADC2_VECTOR__)
308 #elif defined(ADC2_AddressBase)
309  #define __ADC2_VECTOR__ 22 ///< irq22 - ADC2 end of conversion & analog watchdog interrupts (shared with \__ADC1_VECTOR__)
310 #endif
311 #if defined(TIM4_AddressBase)
312  #define __TIM4_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__ 23 ///< irq23 - TIM4 Update/Overflow interrupt (shared with \__TIM6_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__)
313 #elif defined(TIM6_AddressBase)
314  #define __TIM6_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__ 23 ///< irq23 - TIM6 Update/Overflow interrupt (shared with \__TIM4_UPD_OVF_VECTOR__)
315 #endif
316 #define __FLASH_VECTOR__ 24 ///< irq24 - flash interrupt
317

320 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
321  DEFINITION OF STM8 PERIPHERAL REGISTERS
322 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
323 
324 //------------------------
325 // General purpose input/output pins (_PORTx)
326 //------------------------
327 #if defined(_DOXYGEN) || defined(PORTA_AddressBase) || defined(PORTB_AddressBase) || defined(PORTC_AddressBase) || defined(PORTD_AddressBase) || defined(PORTE_AddressBase) || defined(PORTF_AddressBase) || defined(PORTG_AddressBase) || defined(PORTH_AddressBase) || defined(PORTI_AddressBase)
328 
329  /** @brief structure for controlling pins in PORT mode (_PORTx) */
330  typedef struct {
331 
332  /** @brief Port x output data register (_PORTx_ODR) */
333  struct {
334  _BITS PIN0 : 1; ///< pin 0 output control
335  _BITS PIN1 : 1; ///< pin 1 output control
336  _BITS PIN2 : 1; ///< pin 2 output control
337  _BITS PIN3 : 1; ///< pin 3 output control
338  _BITS PIN4 : 1; ///< pin 4 output control
339  _BITS PIN5 : 1; ///< pin 5 output control
340  _BITS PIN6 : 1; ///< pin 6 output control
341  _BITS PIN7 : 1; ///< pin 7 output control
342  } ODR;
343 
344  /** @brief Port x input data register (_PORTx_IDR) */
345  struct {
346  _BITS PIN0 : 1; ///< pin 0 input control
347  _BITS PIN1 : 1; ///< pin 1 input control
348  _BITS PIN2 : 1; ///< pin 2 input control
349  _BITS PIN3 : 1; ///< pin 3 input control
350  _BITS PIN4 : 1; ///< pin 4 input control
351  _BITS PIN5 : 1; ///< pin 5 input control
352  _BITS PIN6 : 1; ///< pin 6 input control
353  _BITS PIN7 : 1; ///< pin 7 input control
354  } IDR;
355 
356  /** @brief Port x data direction data register (_PORTx_DDR) */
357  struct {
358  _BITS PIN0 : 1; ///< pin 0 direction control
359  _BITS PIN1 : 1; ///< pin 1 direction control
360  _BITS PIN2 : 1; ///< pin 2 direction control
361  _BITS PIN3 : 1; ///< pin 3 direction control
362  _BITS PIN4 : 1; ///< pin 4 direction control
363  _BITS PIN5 : 1; ///< pin 5 direction control
364  _BITS PIN6 : 1; ///< pin 6 direction control
365  _BITS PIN7 : 1; ///< pin 7 direction control
366  } DDR;
367 
368  /** @brief Port x control register 1 (_PORTx_CR1) */
369  struct {
370  _BITS PIN0 : 1; ///< pin 0 control register 1
371  _BITS PIN1 : 1; ///< pin 1 control register 1
372  _BITS PIN2 : 1; ///< pin 2 control register 1
373  _BITS PIN3 : 1; ///< pin 3 control register 1
374  _BITS PIN4 : 1; ///< pin 4 control register 1
375  _BITS PIN5 : 1; ///< pin 5 control register 1
376  _BITS PIN6 : 1; ///< pin 6 control register 1
377  _BITS PIN7 : 1; ///< pin 7 control register 1
378  } CR1;
379 
380  /** @brief Port x control register 1 (_PORTx_CR2) */
381  struct {
382  _BITS PIN0 : 1; ///< pin 0 control register 2
383  _BITS PIN1 : 1; ///< pin 1 control register 2
384  _BITS PIN2 : 1; ///< pin 2 control register 2
385  _BITS PIN3 : 1; ///< pin 3 control register 2
386  _BITS PIN4 : 1; ///< pin 4 control register 2
387  _BITS PIN5 : 1; ///< pin 5 control register 2
388  _BITS PIN6 : 1; ///< pin 6 control register 2
389  _BITS PIN7 : 1; ///< pin 7 control register 2
390  } CR2;
391 
392  } _PORT_t;
393 
394  /* Pointer to port A registers */
395  #if defined(PORTA_AddressBase)
396  #define _PORTA _SFR(_PORT_t, PORTA_AddressBase) ///< port A struct/bit access
397  #define _PORTA_ODR _SFR(uint8_t, PORTA_AddressBase+0x00) ///< port A output register
398  #define _PORTA_IDR _SFR(uint8_t, PORTA_AddressBase+0x01) ///< port A input register
399  #define _PORTA_DDR _SFR(uint8_t, PORTA_AddressBase+0x02) ///< port A direction register
400  #define _PORTA_CR1 _SFR(uint8_t, PORTA_AddressBase+0x03) ///< port A control register 1
401  #define _PORTA_CR2 _SFR(uint8_t, PORTA_AddressBase+0x04) ///< port A control register 2
402  #endif
403

475  #if defined(PORTI_AddressBase)
476  #define _PORTI _SFR(_PORT_t, PORTI_AddressBase) ///< port I struct/bit access
477  #define _PORTI_ODR _SFR(uint8_t, PORTI_AddressBase+0x00) ///< port I output register
478  #define _PORTI_IDR _SFR(uint8_t, PORTI_AddressBase+0x01) ///< port I input register
479  #define _PORTI_DDR _SFR(uint8_t, PORTI_AddressBase+0x02) ///< port I direction register
480  #define _PORTI_CR1 _SFR(uint8_t, PORTI_AddressBase+0x03) ///< port I control register 1
481  #define _PORTI_CR2 _SFR(uint8_t, PORTI_AddressBase+0x04) ///< port I control register 2
482  #endif
483 
484 
485  /* PORT Module Reset Values (all ports) */
486  #define _PORT_ODR_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< port output register reset value
487  #define _PORT_DDR_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< port direction register reset value
488  #define _PORT_CR1_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< port control register 1 reset value
489  #define _PORT_CR2_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< port control register 2 reset value
490

492  /* access pins in registers (all ports) */
493  #define _PORT_PIN0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< port bit mask for pin 0 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)
494  #define _PORT_PIN1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< port bit mask for pin 1 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)
495  #define _PORT_PIN2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< port bit mask for pin 2 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)
496  #define _PORT_PIN3 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< port bit mask for pin 3 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)
497  #define _PORT_PIN4 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< port bit mask for pin 4 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)
498  #define _PORT_PIN5 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< port bit mask for pin 5 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)
499  #define _PORT_PIN6 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< port bit mask for pin 6 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)
500  #define _PORT_PIN7 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 7)) ///< port bit mask for pin 7 (in _PORTx_ODR, _PORTx_IDR, _PORTx_DDR, _PORTx_CR1, _PORTx_CR2)

506 //------------------------
507 // Non-volative memory (_FLASH)
508 //------------------------
509 #if defined(_DOXYGEN) || defined(FLASH_AddressBase)
510 
511  /** @brief struct to control write/erase of flash memory (_FLASH) */
512  typedef struct {
513 
514  /** @brief Flash control register 1 (_FLASH_CR1) */
515  struct {
516  _BITS FIX : 1; ///< Fixed Byte programming time
517  _BITS IE : 1; ///< Flash Interrupt enable
518  _BITS AHALT : 1; ///< Power-down in Active-halt mode
519  _BITS HALT : 1; ///< Power-down in Halt mode
520  _BITS : 4; // Reserved
521  } CR1;
522 
523 
524  /** @brief Flash control register 2 (_FLASH_CR2) */
525  struct {
526  _BITS PRG : 1; ///< Standard block programming
527  _BITS : 3; // Reserved
528  _BITS FPRG : 1; ///< Fast block programming
529  _BITS ERASE : 1; ///< Block erasing
530  _BITS WPRG : 1; ///< Word programming
531  _BITS OPT : 1; ///< Write option bytes
532  } CR2;
533 
534 
535  /** @brief Complementary flash control register 2 (_FLASH_NCR2) */
536  struct {
537  _BITS NPRG : 1; ///< Standard block programming
538  _BITS : 3; // Reserved
539  _BITS NFPRG : 1; ///< Fast block programming
540  _BITS NERASE : 1; ///< Block erasing
541  _BITS NWPRG : 1; ///< Word programming
542  _BITS NOPT : 1; ///< Write option bytes
543  } NCR2;
544 
545 
546  /** @brief Flash protection register (_FLASH_FPR) */
547  struct {
548  _BITS WPB : 6; ///< User boot code area protection
549  _BITS : 2; // Reserved
550  } FPR;
551 
552 
553  /** @brief Complementary flash protection register (_FLASH_NFPR) */
554  struct {
555  _BITS NWPB : 6; ///< User boot code area protection
556  _BITS : 2; // Reserved
557  } NFPR;
558 
559 
560  /** @brief Flash status register (_FLASH_IAPSR) */
561  struct {
562  _BITS WR_PG_DIS : 1; ///< Write attempted to protected page flag
563  _BITS PUL : 1; ///< Flash Program memory unlocked flag
564  _BITS EOP : 1; ///< End of programming (write or erase operation) flag
565  _BITS DUL : 1; ///< Data EEPROM area unlocked flag
566  _BITS : 2; // Reserved, forced by hardware to 0
567  _BITS HVOFF : 1; ///< End of high voltage flag
568  _BITS : 1; // Reserved
569  } IAPSR;
570 
571 
572  /** @brief Reserved registers (2B) */
573  uint8_t res [2];
574 
575 
576  /** @brief Flash program memory unprotecting key register (_FLASH_PUKR) */
577  struct {
578  _BITS PUK : 8; ///< Program memory write unlock key
579  } PUKR;
580 
581 
582  /** @brief Reserved register (1B) */
583  uint8_t res2 [1];
584 
585 
586  /** @brief Data EEPROM unprotection key register (_FLASH_DUKR) */
587  struct {
588  _BITS DUK : 8; ///< Data EEPROM write unlock key
589  } DUKR;
590 
591  } _FLASH_t;
592 
593  /* Pointer to flash registers */
594  #define _FLASH _SFR(_FLASH_t, FLASH_AddressBase) ///< Flash struct/bit access
595  #define _FLASH_CR1 _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x00) ///< Flash control register 1
596  #define _FLASH_CR2 _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x01) ///< Flash control register 2
597  #define _FLASH_NCR2 _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x02) ///< complementary Flash control register 2
598  #define _FLASH_FPR _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x03) ///< Flash protection register
599  #define _FLASH_NFPR _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x04) ///< complementary Flash protection register
600  #define _FLASH_IAPSR _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x05) ///< Flash status register
601  // reserved (2B)
602  #define _FLASH_PUKR _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x08) ///< Flash program memory unprotecting key register
603  // reserved (1B)
604  #define _FLASH_DUKR _SFR(uint8_t, FLASH_AddressBase+0x0A) ///< Data EEPROM unprotection key register
605 
606 
607  /* FLASH Module Reset Values */
608  #define _FLASH_CR1_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< Flash control register 1 reset value
609  #define _FLASH_CR2_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< Flash control register 2 reset value
610  #define _FLASH_NCR2_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0xFF) ///< complementary Flash control register 2 reset value
611  #define _FLASH_FRR_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< Flash protection register reset value
612  #define _FLASH_NFRR_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0xFF) ///< Flash Complementary protection register reset value
613  #define _FLASH_IAPSR_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x40) ///< Flash status register reset value
614  #define _FLASH_PUKR_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< Flash program memory unprotecting key reset value
615  #define _FLASH_DUKR_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0x00) ///< Data EEPROM unprotection key reset value
616 
617 
618  /* Flash control register 1 (_FLASH_CR1) */
619  #define _FLASH_CR1_FIX ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< Fixed Byte programming time [0]
620  #define _FLASH_CR1_IE ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< Flash Interrupt enable [0]
621  #define _FLASH_CR1_AHALT ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< Power-down in Active-halt mode [0]
622  #define _FLASH_CR1_HALT ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< Power-down in Halt mode [0]
623  // reserved [7:4]
624 
625  /* Flash control register 2 and complement (_FLASH_CR2 and _FLASH_NCR2) */
626  #define _FLASH_CR2_PRG ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< Standard block programming [0] (in _FLASH_CR2 and _FLASH_NCR2)
627  // reserved [3:1]
628  #define _FLASH_CR2_FPRG ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< Fast block programming [0] (in _FLASH_CR2 and _FLASH_NCR2)
629  #define _FLASH_CR2_ERASE ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< Block erasing [0] (in _FLASH_CR2 and _FLASH_NCR2)
630  #define _FLASH_CR2_WPRG ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< Word programming [0] (in _FLASH_CR2 and _FLASH_NCR2)
631  #define _FLASH_CR2_OPT ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 7)) ///< Write option bytes [0] (in _FLASH_CR2 and _FLASH_NCR2)
632 
633  /* Flash protection register and complement (_FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR) */
634  #define _FLASH_FPR_WPB ((uint8_t) (0x3F << 0)) ///< User boot code area protection [5:0] (in _FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR)
635  #define _FLASH_FPR_WPB0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< User boot code area protection [0] (in _FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR)
636  #define _FLASH_FPR_WPB1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< User boot code area protection [1] (in _FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR)
637  #define _FLASH_FPR_WPB2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< User boot code area protection [2] (in _FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR)
638  #define _FLASH_FPR_WPB3 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< User boot code area protection [3] (in _FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR)
639  #define _FLASH_FPR_WPB4 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< User boot code area protection [4] (in _FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR)
640  #define _FLASH_FPR_WPB5 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< User boot code area protection [5] (in _FLASH_FPR and _FLASH_NFPR)
641  // reserved [7:6]
642 
643  /* Flash status register (_FLASH_IAPSR) */
644  #define _FLASH_IAPSR_WR_PG_DIS ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< Write attempted to protected page flag [0]
645  #define _FLASH_IAPSR_PUL ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< Flash Program memory unlocked flag [0]
646  #define _FLASH_IAPSR_EOP ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< End of programming (write or erase operation) flag [0]
647  #define _FLASH_IAPSR_DUL ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< Data EEPROM area unlocked flag [0]
648  // reserved [5:4]
649  #define _FLASH_IAPSR_HVOFF ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< End of high voltage flag [0]
650  // reserved [7]
651 
652 #endif // FLASH_AddressBase

696  #define _EXTI_CR1_PAIS1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port A [1]
697  #define _EXTI_CR1_PBIS ((uint8_t) (0x03 << 2)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port B [1:0]
698  #define _EXTI_CR1_PBIS0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port B [0]
699  #define _EXTI_CR1_PBIS1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port B [1]
700  #define _EXTI_CR1_PCIS ((uint8_t) (0x03 << 4)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port C [1:0]

702  #define _EXTI_CR1_PCIS1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port C [1]

704  #define _EXTI_CR1_PDIS0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port D [0]
705  #define _EXTI_CR1_PDIS1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 7)) ///< External interrupt sensitivity for Port D [1]

709  #define _EXTI_CR2_PEIS0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< Port E external interrupt sensitivity [0] (in _EXTI_CR2)

766  _BITS HSIRDY : 1; ///< High speed internal oscillator ready flag
767  _BITS FHWU : 1; ///< Fast wakeup from Halt/Active-halt modes enable

769  _BITS LSIRDY : 1; ///< Low speed internal oscillator ready flag

905  #define _CLK_PCKENR2_RESET_VALUE ((uint8_t) 0xFF) ///< Peripheral clock gating register 2 reset value

914  #define _CLK_ICKR_HSIRDY ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< High speed internal oscillator ready [0]
915  #define _CLK_ICKR_FHWU ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< Fast wakeup from Halt/Active-halt modes [0]
916  #define _CLK_ICKR_LSIEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< Low speed internal RC oscillator enable [0]
917  #define _CLK_ICKR_LSIRDY ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< Low speed internal oscillator ready [0]
918  #define _CLK_ICKR_REGAH ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< Regulator power off in Active-halt mode [0]
919  // reserved [7:6]
920 
921  /* External clock register (_CLK_ECKR) */
922  #define _CLK_ECKR_HSEEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< High speed external crystal oscillator enable [0]
923  #define _CLK_ECKR_HSERDY ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< High speed external crystal oscillator ready [0]
924  // reserved [7:2]
925 
926  /* Clock master switch register (_CLK_SWR) */
927  #define _CLK_SWR_SWI_HSI ((uint8_t) 0xE1) ///< write to CLK_SWR for HSI clock
928  #define _CLK_SWR_SWI_LSI ((uint8_t) 0xD2) ///< write to CLK_SWR for LSI clock
929  #define _CLK_SWR_SWI_HSE ((uint8_t) 0xB4) ///< write to CLK_SWR for HSE clock
930 
931  /* Switch control register (_CLK_SWCR) */
932  #define _CLK_SWCR_SWBSY ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< Switch busy flag [0]
933  #define _CLK_SWCR_SWEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< Switch start/stop enable [0]
934  #define _CLK_SWCR_SWIEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< Clock switch interrupt enable [0]
935  #define _CLK_SWCR_SWIF ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< Clock switch interrupt flag [0]
936  // reserved [7:4]
937 
938  /* Clock divider register (_CLK_CKDIVR) */
939  #define _CLK_CKDIVR_CPUDIV ((uint8_t) (0x07 << 0)) ///< CPU clock prescaler [2:0]
940  #define _CLK_CKDIVR_CPUDIV0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< CPU clock prescaler [0]
941  #define _CLK_CKDIVR_CPUDIV1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< CPU clock prescaler [1]
942  #define _CLK_CKDIVR_CPUDIV2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< CPU clock prescaler [2]
943  #define _CLK_CKDIVR_HSIDIV ((uint8_t) (0x03 << 3)) ///< High speed internal clock prescaler [1:0]
944  #define _CLK_CKDIVR_HSIDIV0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< High speed internal clock prescaler [0]
945  #define _CLK_CKDIVR_HSIDIV1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< High speed internal clock prescaler [1]
946  // reserved [7:5]
947 
948  /* Peripheral clock gating register 1 (_CLK_PCKENR1) */
949  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_I2C ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< clock enable I2C [0]
950  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_SPI ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< clock enable SPI [0]
951  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_UART1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< clock enable UART1 [0]
952  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_UART2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< clock enable UART2 [0]
953  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_TIM4_TIM6 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< clock enable TIM4/TIM6 [0]
954  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_TIM2_TIM5 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< clock enable TIM2/TIM5 [0]
955  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_TIM3 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< clock enable TIM3 [0]
956  #define _CLK_PCKENR1_TIM1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 7)) ///< clock enable TIM1 [0]
957 
958  /* Clock security system register (_CLK_CSSR) */
959  #define _CLK_CSSR_CSSEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< Clock security system enable [0]
960  #define _CLK_CSSR_AUX ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< Auxiliary oscillator connected to master clock [0]
961  #define _CLK_CSSR_CSSDIE ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< Clock security system detection interrupt enable [0]
962  #define _CLK_CSSR_CSSD ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< Clock security system detection [0]
963  // reserved [7:4]
964 
965  /* Configurable clock output register (_CLK_CCOR) */
966  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCOEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< Configurable clock output enable [0]
967  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCOSEL ((uint8_t) (0x0F << 1)) ///< Configurable clock output selection [3:0]
968  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCOSEL0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< Configurable clock output selection [0]
969  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCOSEL1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< Configurable clock output selection [1]
970  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCOSEL2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< Configurable clock output selection [2]
971  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCOSEL3 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< Configurable clock output selection [3]
972  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCORDY ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< Configurable clock output ready [0]
973  #define _CLK_CCOR_CCOBSY ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< Configurable clock output busy [0]
974  // reserved [7]
975 
976  /* Peripheral clock gating register 2 (_CLK_PCKENR2) */
977  // reserved [1:0]
978  #define _CLK_PCKENR2_AWU ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< clock enable AWU [0]
979  #define _CLK_PCKENR2_ADC ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< clock enable ADC [0]
980  // reserved [6:4]
981  #define _CLK_PCKENR2_CAN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 7)) ///< clock enable CAN [0]
982 
983  /* HSI clock calibration trimming register (_CLK_HSITRIMR) */
984  #define _CLK_HSITRIMR_HSITRIM ((uint8_t) (0x0F << 0)) ///< HSI trimming value (some devices only support 3 bits, see DS!) [3:0]
985  #define _CLK_HSITRIMR_HSITRIM0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< HSI trimming value [0]
986  #define _CLK_HSITRIMR_HSITRIM1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< HSI trimming value [1]
987  #define _CLK_HSITRIMR_HSITRIM2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< HSI trimming value [2]
988  #define _CLK_HSITRIMR_HSITRIM3 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< HSI trimming value [3]
989  // reserved [7:4]
990 
991  /* SWIM clock control register (_CLK_SWIMCCR) */
992  #define _CLK_SWIMCCR_SWIMCLK ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< SWIM clock divider [0]
993  // reserved [7:2]
994 
995 #endif // CLK_AddressBase

1237  /** @brief struct for controlling SPI module (_SPI) */
1238  typedef struct {
1239

1241  struct {
1242  _BITS CPHA : 1; ///< Clock phase
1243  _BITS CPOL : 1; ///< Clock polarity
1244  _BITS MSTR : 1; ///< Master/slave selection
1245  _BITS BR : 3; ///< Baudrate control
1246  _BITS SPE : 1; ///< SPI enable
1247  _BITS LSBFIRST : 1; ///< Frame format
1248  } CR1;
1249 
1250 
1251  /** @brief SPI control register 2 (_SPI_CR2) */
1252  struct {
1253  _BITS SSI : 1; ///< Internal slave select
1254  _BITS SSM : 1; ///< Software slave management
1255  _BITS RXONLY : 1; ///< Receive only
1256  _BITS : 1; // Reserved
1257  _BITS CRCNEXT : 1; ///< Transmit CRC next
1258  _BITS CRCEN : 1; ///< Hardware CRC calculation enable
1259  _BITS BDOE : 1; ///< Input/Output enable in bidirectional mode
1260  _BITS BDM : 1; ///< Bidirectional data mode enable
1261  } CR2;
1262 
1263 
1264  /** @brief SPI interrupt control register (_SPI_ICR) */
1265  struct {
1266  _BITS : 4; // Reserved
1267  _BITS WKIE : 1; ///< Wakeup interrupt enable
1268  _BITS ERRIE : 1; ///< Error interrupt enable
1269  _BITS RXIE : 1; ///< Rx buffer not empty interrupt enable
1270  _BITS TXIE : 1; ///< Tx buffer empty interrupt enable
1271  } ICR;
1272 
1273 
1274  /** @brief SPI status register (_SPI_SR) */
1275  struct {
1276  _BITS RXNE : 1; ///< Receive buffer not empty
1277  _BITS TXE : 1; ///< Transmit buffer empty
1278  _BITS : 1; // Reserved
1279  _BITS WKUP : 1; ///< Wakeup flag
1280  _BITS CRCERR : 1; ///< CRC error flag
1281  _BITS MODF : 1; ///< Mode fault
1282  _BITS OVR : 1; ///< Overrun flag
1283  _BITS BSY : 1; ///< Busy flag
1284  } SR;
1285 
1286 
1287  /** @brief SPI data register (_SPI_DR) */
1288  struct {
1289  _BITS DATA : 8; ///< SPI data
1290  } DR;
1291 
1292 
1293  /** @brief SPI CRC polynomial register (_SPI_CRCPR) */
1294  struct {
1295  _BITS CRCPOLY : 8; ///< CRC polynomial register
1296  } CRCPR;
1297 
1298 
1299  /** @brief SPI Rx CRC register (_SPI_RXCRCR) */
1300  struct {
1301  _BITS RxCRC : 8; ///< Rx CRC Register
1302  } RXCRCR;
1303 
1304 
1305  /** @brief SPI Tx CRC register (_SPI_TXCRCR) */
1306  struct {
1307  _BITS TxCRC : 8; ///< Tx CRC register
1308  } TXCRCR;
1309 
1310  } _SPI_t;
1311 
1312  /// register for SPI control
1313  #define _SPI _SFR(_SPI_t, SPI_AddressBase) ///< SPI struct/bit access
1314  #define _SPI_CR1 _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x00) ///< SPI control register 1
1315  #define _SPI_CR2 _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x01) ///< SPI control register 2
1316  #define _SPI_ICR _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x02) ///< SPI interrupt control register
1317  #define _SPI_SR _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x03) ///< SPI status register
1318  #define _SPI_DR _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x04) ///< SPI data register
1319  #define _SPI_CRCPR _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x05) ///< SPI CRC polynomial register
1320  #define _SPI_RXCRCR _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x06) ///< SPI Rx CRC register
1321  #define _SPI_TXCRCR _SFR(uint8_t, SPI_AddressBase+0x07) ///< SPI Tx CRC register

1703  _BITS REN : 1; ///< Receiver enable

1708  _BITS TIEN : 1; ///< Transmitter interrupt enable

2464  #define _UART4_CR3_CKEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< UART4 Clock enable [0]
2465  #define _UART4_CR3_STOP ((uint8_t) (0x03 << 4)) ///< UART4 STOP bits [1:0]
2466  #define _UART4_CR3_STOP0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< UART4 STOP bits [0]
2467  #define _UART4_CR3_STOP1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< UART4 STOP bits [1]
2468  #define _UART4_CR3_LINEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< UART4 LIN mode enable [0]
2469  // reserved [7]
2470 
2471  /* UART4 Control register 4 (_UART4_CR4) */
2472  #define _UART4_CR4_ADD ((uint8_t) (0x0F << 0)) ///< UART4 Address of the UART node [3:0]
2473  #define _UART4_CR4_ADD0 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< UART4 Address of the UART node [0]
2474  #define _UART4_CR4_ADD1 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< UART4 Address of the UART node [1]
2475  #define _UART4_CR4_ADD2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< UART4 Address of the UART node [2]
2476  #define _UART4_CR4_ADD3 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< UART4 Address of the UART node [3]
2477  #define _UART4_CR4_LBDF ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< UART4 LIN Break Detection Flag [0]
2478  #define _UART4_CR4_LBDL ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< UART4 LIN Break Detection Length [0]
2479  #define _UART4_CR4_LBDIEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< UART4 LIN Break Detection Interrupt Enable [0]
2480  // reserved [7]
2481 
2482  /* UART4 Control register 5 (_UART4_CR5) */
2483  // reserved [0]
2484  #define _UART4_CR5_IREN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< UART4 IrDA mode Enable [0]
2485  #define _UART4_CR5_IRLP ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< UART4 IrDA Low Power [0]
2486  #define _UART4_CR5_HDSEL ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< UART4 Half-Duplex Selection [0]
2487  #define _UART4_CR5_NACK ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< UART4 Smartcard NACK enable [0]
2488  #define _UART4_CR5_SCEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< UART4 Smartcard mode enable [0]
2489  // reserved [7:6]
2490 
2491  /* UART4 Control register 6 (_UART4_CR6) */
2492  #define _UART4_CR6_LSF ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< UART4 LIN Sync Field [0]
2493  #define _UART4_CR6_LHDF ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 1)) ///< UART4 LIN Header Detection Flag [0]
2494  #define _UART4_CR6_LHDIEN ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< UART4 LIN Header Detection Interrupt Enable [0]
2495  // reserved [3]

2497  #define _UART4_CR6_LSLV ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< UART4 LIN Slave Enable [0]
2498  // reserved [6]

6144  /* CAN master control register (_CAN_MCR) */
6145  #define _CAN_MCR_INRQ ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 0)) ///< CAN Channel Initialization Request [0]

6147  #define _CAN_MCR_TXFP ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 2)) ///< CAN Channel Transmit FIFO Priority [0]
6148  #define _CAN_MCR_RFLM ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< CAN Channel Receive FIFO Locked Mode [0]
6149  #define _CAN_MCR_NART ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 4)) ///< CAN Channel No Automatic Retransmission [0]
6150  #define _CAN_MCR_AWUM ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< CAN Channel Automatic Wakeup Mode [0]
6151  #define _CAN_MCR_ABOM ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< CAN Channel Automatic Bus-Off Management [0]
6152  #define _CAN_MCR_TTCM ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 7)) ///< CAN Channel Time Triggered Communication Mode [0]

6158  #define _CAN_MSR_WKUI ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 3)) ///< CAN Wakeup Interrupt [0]

6160  #define _CAN_MSR_RX ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 5)) ///< CAN Receive [0]
6161  // reserved [7:6]

6170  #define _CAN_TSR_TXOK2 ((uint8_t) (0x01 << 6)) ///< CAN Transmission ok for Mailbox 2 [0]
